Here is the Julia code to solve your problem:

```julia
function clean_column(col)
    # lowercasing it
    col = lowercase(col);
    # stripping leading and trailing whitespaces
    col = strip(col);
    # replacing spaces and hyphens with underscore
    col = replace(col, " " => "_");
    col = replace(col, "-" => "_");
    return col;
end
```
You can use this function like so:

```julia
column_name = clean_column("My Column");
println(column_name); # This should print "my_column"
```
